# Third-Party Licenses

Cairn is distributed as a compiled macOS application that statically links a
number of open-source Rust crates. This document reproduces the license text
and attribution notices for every third-party crate compiled into the shipped
binary, as required by those licenses — in particular the Apache License 2.0
§4(d), which requires reproducing the attribution notices of Apache-licensed
dependencies (tauri, reqwest, tokio, serde, hyper, h2, and others; many of
these are dual-licensed `MIT OR Apache-2.0`, and the full Apache-2.0 text is
reproduced below).

Cairn's own source code is licensed under the MIT License; see the `LICENSE`
file at the repository root. The notices below cover the bundled dependencies
only.

This file is generated mechanically from the resolved Cargo dependency graph
for the macOS targets. The bundled crates are covered by the following
licenses (crate counts are de-duplicated per license):

